The user chose strategy A (simplify), I implemented it, and now they're saying they didn't want that. They want to go back to the C++23 version. Let me restore the file to the `#include <print>` version.

But wait - they said "верни обратно чтобы он был по тому стандарту С++ который был до этого". The version "before" I changed it was:

```cpp
#include <print>

int main()
{
    std::println("Hello, World!");
}
```

That was the version I wrote after the `import std;` version failed. The user wants that back. Let me restore it.

```cpp
#include <print>

int main()
{
    std::println("Hello, World!");
}
```

